Stable versions on Packagist are immutable: once published, their source and dist
references cannot change. This protects downstream users from a published version
silently swapping its contents (e.g. via a re-tag or force-push).

If the change in your repository was intentional and you want the new code to be
available to users, please tag a new version with the fix and push it.

Ideally you should also restore the tag to the previous commit reference to
bring the repository back in line with what Packagist.org shows and avoid
confusing people.

